      • checkSimplyLive

        public static java.util.List<Transition> checkSimplyLive(PetriNet pn,
                                                         Transition transition)
        Check if the given transition is simply live. This means that the transition can fire in at least one reachable state and thus is not dead.
        Parameters:
        pn - The Petri net that should be examined.
        transition - The transition that is checked.
        Returns:
        A firable firing sequence that ends with the given transition, or null.

      • checkWeaklyLive

        public static boolean checkWeaklyLive(PetriNet pn,
                                      Transition transition)
                               throws UnboundedException
        Check if the given transition is weakly live. This means that there exists an infinite fire sequence which fires the transition infinitely often.
        Parameters:
        pn - The Petri net that should be examined.
        transition - The transition that is checked.
        Returns:
        True if the transition is weakly live, else false.
        Throws:
        UnboundedException - If the reachability graph is unbounded.

      • checkStronglyLive

        public static boolean checkStronglyLive(PetriNet pn,
                                        Transition transition)
                                 throws UnboundedException
        Check if the given transition is strongly live. This means that for every reachable state there exists a fire sequence after which this transition is activated.
        Parameters:
        pn - The Petri net that should be examined.
        transition - The transition that is checked.
        Returns:
        True if the transition is strongly live, else false.
        Throws:
        UnboundedException - If the reachability graph is unbounded.

      • findKillingFireSequence

        public static java.util.List<Transition> findKillingFireSequence(PetriNet pn,
                                                                 Transition transition)
                                                          throws UnboundedException
        Find a firing sequence after which the given transition can never fire again. Such a firing sequence exists if and only if the given transition is not strongly live.
        Parameters:
        pn - The Petri net that should be examined.
        transition - The transition that is checked.
        Returns:
        null if the transition is strongly live, else a firing sequence after which it can no longer fire.
        Throws:
        UnboundedException - If the reachability graph is unbounded.
